By Steph Cockroft for MailOnline A jilted man who stabbed his teenage love rival to death after discovering he was dating his ex-girlfriend has been jailed for life. Will Blencowe, 21, attacked 17-year-old Connor Tremble in a jealous rage at his flat the day before Valentine’s Day. Blencowe, from Banbury, Oxfordshire, had travelled to the victim's flat in Oxford after discovering was seeing his ex-girlfriend Aimee Harrison, 20. After the 'vicious' attack, Blencowe fled more than 50 miles away, leaving the victim with multiple stab wounds, including in the lung, back and buttocks. Will Blencowe, 21, pictured left, from Banbury, Oxfordshire, has been jailed for life with a minimum of 23 years for murdering 17-year-old Connor Tremble, pictured right, from Oxford in a jealous rage
